# SYS-LIC-GATE-Z2
## Replay Queue Controller

Version: 2.0

---

# Overview

SYS-LIC-GATE-Z2 is the autonomous replay controller for the HyperSync License Operating System.

Its responsibility is to safely recover failed license operations by evaluating replay eligibility, enforcing deterministic retry policies, scheduling exponential backoff, and dispatching replay requests back into the execution pipeline.

Rather than acting as a simple retry mechanism, Gate Z2 operates as a controlled state machine that guarantees replay integrity while preventing duplicate execution and infinite retry loops.

---

# Architectural Purpose

Gate Z2 is responsible for:

• Replay Queue Management

• Replay Eligibility Validation

• Retry Contract Enforcement

• Exponential Backoff Scheduling

• Replay Dispatch

• Replay State Commitment

• Governance Evidence Generation

---

# Core Responsibilities

The controller performs the following operational sequence:

- Load replay queue records
- Validate replay eligibility
- Verify retry limits
- Calculate replay attempt schedule
- Compute next replay timestamp
- Dispatch replay to the Execution Worker
- Confirm replay with the License Lifecycle Controller
- Commit operational replay state
- Append immutable governance evidence

Every replay follows a deterministic execution contract.

