# Replay Policy

Gate Z2 enforces a bounded replay strategy using exponential backoff.

Replay attempts are scheduled using increasing retry intervals to reduce repeated failures while maintaining automatic recovery.

Example policy:

Attempt 1 → 2 minutes

Attempt 2 → 4 minutes

Attempt 3 → 8 minutes

Attempt 4 → 16 minutes

Attempt 5 → 60 minutes

After the configured retry threshold is reached, replay authority is transferred to the DeadLetter Controller.

